metadata.name: Curtains #93
metadata.description:
Curtains

While learning more about flow fields, as an intermediate step, the first version of this came out.
The artwork creates a set of lines; the first point of the lines are anchors, which can be in a straight line, sinus wave, or tangent function.
The second point is set by calculating the angle from the first using Perlin noise.

The project features 10 different hand-picked color schemes.

Actions:
--------------
Press [s] to save
--------------


Created using p5.js

metadata.description:
Rebirth of the Phoenix

This is the first project in 2023 and is inspired by the fireworks and ancient myths about the new year and celebrations. Old customs still retain full vitality in this land, and new hopes rebirth from the ashes.

--------------------------

This is also the first work of a larger portfolio of work 'State of Coherence' (SoC) which explores and describes the coherence of people, cultures and the objective world.

--------------------------

metadata.name: Morixels Mega Colab #2 #450
Separation in the Night #239
metadata.description:
For this project I was strongly inspired by the paintings of Mark Rothko, Jackson Pollock, Kazemir Malevich, but mostly token refers to the works of one of the largest figures of the European avant-garde, Paul Klee. I wanted to convey that complex color mood and atmosphere that artist achieved with oil paints. 
I have been working with color palettes and functions for a long time to make complex transitions and gradients. This code has really huge potential for a wide diversity of artworks and I would like to see as many interesting variations as possible. Enjoy<3

Project contains:

•three canvas types : horizontal, vertical, square
•rare features : vertical stripes, posterization
•press "p" to pause animation and play again
•open in tab and press "s" to save .png


Made in P5.js by @Georginerous

metadata.name: Modulacions (audio) #89
metadata.description:
Modulacions (Modulations): modulation with an oscillator (carrier) with an LFO (modulator). 

-The LFO is controlled by  some of fxhash characters

-Some parameters are randomly assigned to each of the possible characters of the fxhash string (0,1,2....X,Y,Z): carrier frequency, maximum and minimum frequencies of the modulator, waveforms, views etc.

-A number of fxhash characters are selected (8,16,24,32, 40 or 48), and in order they are played and displayed using the assigned values.

-Each character is encoded in binary-> the LFO frequency is controlled: 1->maximum frequency, 0->minimum frequency.

Features:
·dark: black (true) or white (false).
·carrier_wave: wave shape of carrier oscillator (sine, square, triangle or sawtooth)
·modulator_mult: value of LFO multiplier.
·modulator_sum: value added to LFO amplitude.
·num_fxhash_chars: number of fxhash characters used (8,16,24,32, 40 or 48)
·bits_display: bits string visualization (3 types)
·carrier_freq_range: frequency range of carrier (low, mid or high).
·frames_per_bit: duration of each bit in frames.(15,20,25 or 30)

-NOTE: Headphones recomended. Some extreme sounds (frequency and amplitude) can be generated.

-p5js and p5.sound

metadata.name: MEGDAZ II #69
metadata.description:
Welcome to Megdaz II - one the most beautiful of all Central High Atlas area of Morocco.

I wanted to create an animated version of Megdaz - subtile movements but still interesting enough to observe the whole scene.

This artwork shows Megdaz as abstract town at different times and places:
- cafe terrace at night
- at the pool
- at the river
- before a mirror
- at the central park
- end of summer
- supper at Emmaus
- at the melting pot
- at the game

The canvas resolution is 4096x4096

--

Generative Art created by Michael Vogt (@neophob).
